# Duhem Verification Definitions — the co-located `.duhem/` suite.
#
# Drop this stanza into your repo's CODEOWNERS file (GitHub reads it
# from the repo root, `.github/`, or `docs/`). It routes every edit
# under `.duhem/` to a verifier reviewer, so a PR that "fixes" a
# failing verdict by weakening its own check still passes through
# review. This is the lightweight self-weakening guard from
# `docs/duhem-spec.md` §11.2 (Duhem-as-tool) — review discipline, not a
# structural boundary. Pair it with hub-recorded verdicts (`duhem
# ship`) for the self-attestation guard.
#
# Replace @<org>/duhem-verifier with the team or user that owns
# verification review in your org. Requires branch protection with
# "Require review from Code Owners" enabled to have teeth.

/.duhem/  @<org>/duhem-verifier
